::: {.cell}

:::


*The Estuarine Realm is one of the most threatened in South Africa, in terms of both number of ecosystem types and by area. Of South Africa’s 22 estuarine ecosystem types, 91% are threatened with 5% Critically Endangered, 41% Endangered and 45% Vulnerable. Of total estuarine area, 99% is threatened with 1% Critically Endangered, 72% Endangered and 26% Vulnerable. Unsustainable land and sea use can undermine the benefits from healthy ecosystems and the natural capital that can support a thriving economy ([key message A2](../key-messages/kma2.qmd)).*

![Knysna is one of two estuarine bays inside South Africa and is an example of a Vulnerable system. (© Matt Dubber)](imgs/est_knysna_matt_dubber.jpeg)

